text":"Context","value":"context","line":14,"column":0},"objectives":{"type":"header","text":"Objectives","value":"objectives","line":23,"column":0},"agents":{"type":"header","text":"Agents","value":"agents","line":30,"column":0},"methods":{"type":"header","text":"Methods","value":"methods","line":32,"column":0},"results":{"type":"header","text":"Results","value":"results","line":43,"column":0},"htoed-context":{"type":"header","text":"HTOED Context","value":"htoed-context","line":45,"column":0},"examples-hierarchies":{"type":"header","text":"Examples hierarchies","value":"examples-hierarchies","line":48,"column":0},"excerpts-from-htoed":{"type":"header","text":"Excerpts from HTOED","value":"excerpts-from-htoed","line":68,"column":0}},"fname":"experiment.bias-in-language","updated":1629267256467,"created":1624868888561,"parent":"D7128jwSvEVrDT7EBiIq8","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"d007dffb9feaf90cdaae5abec50ffa49","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"-bias-in-language\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#-bias-in-language\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a> Bias in Language</h1>\n<ul class=\"contains-task-list\">\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> Collect examples of interesting words and categories from Historical Thesaurus</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> Format using tables and embed in Markdown</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> Visualize categories using graphs and/or diagrams</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"overview\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#overview\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Overview</h3>\n<h3 id=\"context\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#context\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Context</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Human languages have developed over thousands of years</li>\n<li>They reflect cultural norms, biases and traditions\n<ul>\n<li>See <a href=\"/placecolor/notes/fY1IaxfskZCKCL4cOn5eQ\">Language about Color</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Such biases include the ways that humans think about nonhumans as 'others'</li>\n<li>Exposing and exploring these biases is useful for thinking about nonhuman <a title=\"Private\" style=\"color: brown\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\">subjectivity (Private)</a>.\n<ul>\n<li>See <a href=\"/placecolor/notes/3s7wzZqzhNXsruHgpaYn1\">Color Vision of Bees</a> for a similar approach using computer software to simulate the color vision of bees.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"objectives\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#objectives\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Objectives</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Demonstrate biases in human language and attempts to classify language, e.g. thesauruses, ontologies, databases.</li>\n<li>Present a curated selection of interesting words related to human and nonhuman place</li>\n<li>Suggest ways of 'exposing' bias in texts by classifying using HTOED categories\n<ul>\n<li>Indicate potential for future work</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"agents\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#agents\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Agents</h4>\n<h3 id=\"methods\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#methods\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Methods</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Introduce the Historical Thesaurus of the Oxford English Dictionary\n<ul>\n<li>Provide important background information</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Collect examples from the HTOED related to human and nonhuman place\n<ul>\n<li>Hierarchies</li>\n<li>Words</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Visualize this information\n<ul>\n<li>Present a selection of interesting/rare words about human and nonhuman place</li>\n<li>Emphasize the underlying assumptions and biases that inform the HTOED categories</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"results\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#results\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Results</h3>\n<h4 id=\"htoed-context\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#htoed-context\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>HTOED Context</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/placecolor/assets/images/2021-08-18-15-57-44.png\"></p>\n<h4 id=\"examples-hierarchies\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#examples-hierarchies\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Examples hierarchies</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/placecolor/assets/images/2021-08-18-14-54-11.png\" alt=\"Example of HTOED categories tree view\"></p>\n<p>Compare different structures to</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The world\n<ul>\n<li>Animals\n<ul>\n<li>By habitat\n<ul>\n<li>Habitat</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Society\n<ul>\n<li>Inhabiting and dwelling\n<ul>\n<li>Inhabited place\n<ul>\n<li>Dwelling-place/abode</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"excerpts-from-htoed\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#excerpts-from-htoed\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Excerpts from HTOED</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/placecolor/assets/images/2021-08-18-15-00-57.png\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>01.05.02.01|01 (n.) Habitat :: dwelling place/shelter</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"/placecolor/assets/images/2021-08-18-15-07-36.png\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>01.05.02.01|01.01 (n.) Habitat :: dwelling place/shelter :: of a wild animal</em></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2